<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Type information &quot;parsing&quot; is very primitive:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - The &#96;RawData&#96; is copied to a buffer owned by &#96;BTFParser&#96; instance.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - The buffer is treated as an array of &#96;uint32&#95;t&#96; values, each value</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   is swapped to use native endianness. This is possible, because</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   of &#96;uint32&#95;t&#96; fields.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - &#96;BTFParser::Types&#96; vector is filled with pointers to buffer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   elements, using &#96;byteSize()&#96; function to slice the buffer at type</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   record boundaries.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - If at some point a type definition with incorrect size (logical size</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   exceeding buffer boundaries) is reached it is not added to the</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Produces a human readable description of a CO-RE relocation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Such relocations are generated by BPF backend, and processed</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// by libbpf&#39;s BPF program loader &#91;1&#93;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="607"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Each relocation record has the following information:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="609"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Relocation kind;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - BTF type ID;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Access string offset in string table.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00612" /><CodeLine lineNumber="612"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00613" /><CodeLine lineNumber="613"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// There are different kinds of relocations, these kinds could be split</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00614" /><CodeLine lineNumber="614"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in three groups:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00615" /><CodeLine lineNumber="615"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - load-time information about types (size, existence),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00616" /><CodeLine lineNumber="616"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#96;BTFParser::symbolize()&#96; output for such relocations uses the template:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00617" /><CodeLine lineNumber="617"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00618" /><CodeLine lineNumber="618"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     &lt;relocation-kind&gt; &#91;&lt;id&gt;&#93; &lt;type-name&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00619" /><CodeLine lineNumber="619"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00620" /><CodeLine lineNumber="620"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   For example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00621" /><CodeLine lineNumber="621"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   - &quot;&lt;type&#95;exists&gt; &#91;7&#93; struct foo&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00622" /><CodeLine lineNumber="622"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   - &quot;&lt;type&#95;size&gt; &#91;7&#93; struct foo&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - load-time information about enums (literal existence, literal value),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#96;BTFParser::symbolize()&#96; output for such relocations uses the template:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00627" /><CodeLine lineNumber="627"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     &lt;relocation-kind&gt; &#91;&lt;id&gt;&#93; &lt;type-name&gt;::&lt;literal-name&gt; = &lt;original-value&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   For example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   - &quot;&lt;enumval&#95;exists&gt; &#91;5&#93; enum foo::U = 1&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   - &quot;&lt;enumval&#95;value&gt; &#91;5&#93; enum foo::V = 2&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - load-time information about fields (e.g. field offset),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#96;BTFParser::symbolize()&#96; output for such relocations uses the template:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     &lt;relocation-kind&gt; &#91;&lt;id&gt;&#93; \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       &lt;type-name&gt;::&#91;N&#93;.&lt;field-1-name&gt;...&lt;field-M-name&gt; \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       (&lt;access string&gt;)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00640" /><CodeLine lineNumber="640"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   For example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00641" /><CodeLine lineNumber="641"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   - &quot;&lt;byte&#95;off&gt; &#91;8&#93; struct bar::&#91;7&#93;.v (7:1)&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00642" /><CodeLine lineNumber="642"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   - &quot;&lt;field&#95;exists&gt; &#91;8&#93; struct bar::v (0:1)&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00643" /><CodeLine lineNumber="643"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00644" /><CodeLine lineNumber="644"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If relocation description is not valid output follows the following pattern:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00645" /><CodeLine lineNumber="645"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00646" /><CodeLine lineNumber="646"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     &lt;relocation-kind&gt; &lt;type-id&gt;::&lt;unprocessedaccess-string&gt; &lt;&lt;error-msg&gt;&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00647" /><CodeLine lineNumber="647"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00648" /><CodeLine lineNumber="648"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00649" /><CodeLine lineNumber="649"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - &quot;&lt;type&#95;sz&gt; &#91;42&#93; &#39;&#39; &lt;unknown type id: 42&gt;&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00651" /><CodeLine lineNumber="651"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - &quot;&lt;byte&#95;off&gt; &#91;4&#93; &#39;0:&#39; &lt;field spec too short&gt;&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00652" /><CodeLine lineNumber="652"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00653" /><CodeLine lineNumber="653"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Additional examples could be found in unit tests, see</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00654" /><CodeLine lineNumber="654"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// llvm/unittests/DebugInfo/BTF/BTFParserTest.cpp.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00655" /><CodeLine lineNumber="655"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00656" /><CodeLine lineNumber="656"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &#91;1&#93; https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/bpf/libbpf/index.html</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/btfparser/#a7db30a1144cd370f595ed6c16904db15"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/btfparser/#a7db30a1144cd370f595ed6c16904db15">BTFParser::symbolize</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/btf/bpffieldreloc">BTF::BPFFieldReloc</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/reloc">Reloc</a>,</span></CodeLine>
